    <h3>Flights to Paris</h3>
    <p>A flight to Paris, the capital of France, is a popular choice for travelers seeking to explore its rich culture, history, and iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, Louvre Museum, and Notre-Dame Cathedral. Paris is well-connected by major international airlines and offers flights from various parts of the world.</p>
   
    <h4>Key Information:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Airports in Paris:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Charles de Gaulle Airport (CDG):</strong> The primary international airport in Paris, located around 25 kilometers north of the city center.</li>
                <li><strong>Orly Airport (ORY):</strong> Located closer to the city center, Orly serves domestic flights and some international routes.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Airlines:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Air France:</strong> Frequent flights to Paris from major cities worldwide.</li>
                <li><strong>Low-Cost Airlines:</strong> Budget-friendly carriers like EasyJet and Ryanair.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Flight Duration:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>From the United States: 7 to 9 hours.</li>
                <li>From Europe: 1 to 3 hours.</li>
                <li>From Asia and Africa: 10 to 13 hours.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Best Time to Book:</strong>
            <p>Book at least 2-3 months in advance for peak seasons. Off-season may offer cheaper flights but colder weather.</p>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Travel Tips:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Visa Requirements:</strong> Check if you need a Schengen visa.</li>
                <li><strong>Jet Lag:</strong> Adjust your sleep schedule before travel.</li>
                <li><strong>Airport Transfers:</strong> Paris has excellent public transport options like RER trains and buses.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    
